All Classes and Interfaces

Classes
Class
Description
ComplexGates
This class provides implementations of several quantum gates in complex form, such as Pauli-X, Pauli-Y, Pauli-Z, and Hadamard gates.
ComplexMatrix
This class represents a matrix of complex numbers and supports basic matrix operations.
ComplexNumber
Represents a complex number with real and imaginary parts.
ComplexObject
ComplexObject serves as the parent class for other complex classes, providing a single location for linear algebra functions to be collected and giving universal access to those methods on each complex class.
ComplexQubit
This class represents a single qubit.
Console
Helper class for reading and writing to the Java console with input validation specific to type requested.
Driver
The main class that drives the JQsim quantum computing simulation.
GateBuilder
The GateBuilder class is responsible for constructing and applying quantum gates to a quantum state vector.
Qops
original_files.Qubit class that contains all the qubit related methods
QubitWire
Represents a quantum qubit wire that stores quantum gates in a queue.
Reader
The Reader class provides methods to load ComplexQubit objects from a file.
StateTracker
The class tracks the state of the quantum system ComplexQubits as a column vector stored in a ComplexMatrix of nx1 dimensions where n is 2 to the power of the number of ComplexQubits.
WorkItem
Represents a work item with an operator and associated control and target values.
WorkQueue
Represents a queue of WorkItem objects with thread-safe operations.
Writer
The Writer class provides methods to save ComplexQubit objects to a file.
